Steps to Create AWS Free-Tier Account
Step 1: Open AWS Sign-Up Page

Visit: https://aws.amazon.com/free

Click “Create a Free Account”.

Step 2: Enter Email and Password

Provide your email address.

Create AWS login password.

Enter AWS Account Name (Example: Manisha-AWS).

Step 3: Choose Account Type

Select Personal Account (recommended for students).

Fill details: full name, address, phone number.

Step 4: Billing Information

Enter valid debit/credit card details.

AWS will take a small refundable amount for verification.

Step 5: Phone Verification

Enter your phone number.

You will receive an OTP or automated call.

Step 6: Select Support Plan

Choose Basic Support – Free.

Step 7: Login to AWS Console

Visit: https://console.aws.amazon.com

Sign in using your email and password.

Step 8: Open the AWS Dashboard

The main dashboard contains services like:

EC2

S3

Lambda

RDS

Take Screenshot of dashboard.
